-- Iraq Signs Unit-Building Contract With South Korea’s Hanwha
-- B y   K h a l i d   A l   A n s a r y
-- 2012-05-26T22:42:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-26/iraq-signs-unit-building-contract-with-south-korea-s-hanwha.html
Iraq signed a contract with  South
Korea ’s Hanwha Engineering & Construction Corp. to build 100,000
residential units in the capital,  Baghdad , according to an e-
mailed statement yesterday from the city’s governor.  Salah Abdul Razzaq, Baghdad’s governor, said more than
30,000 people are registered for the units so far, adding that
the project will secure 100,000 jobs.  Abdul Razzaq said the Iraqi parliament may soon approve $2
billion worth of projects for the Housing Ministry to build
residential units.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Khalid Al-Ansary in Dubai at 
